With Lucid, you can create your own career adventure. We actively support all
our team to initiate innovative ideas and act on them. As a senior hire, you
can look forward to defining the next steps in your career to include
commercial and leadership skills.

** What Sets Us Apart **

We are one of Australia’s largest employee-owned engineering consultancy. Day-
to-day, you will be working with shareholders who will back your ideas and
support your growth. Our culture will help you always feel part of an engaged
team who thrive on challenges and helping each other to deliver outstanding
client outcomes.

** Overview of our employee benefits: **

  * Flexible Work Arrangements: Balance life and work seamlessly. 
  * Career Development Pathway: Accelerate your growth with immersive training that leads the industry. 
  * Employee Share Program: Become an owner in the business and share in the rewards. 
  * Diverse Project Range: Tackle a broad range of exciting projects. 
  * Employee Assistance Program: A support network for your well-being. 
  * Industry Accreditations: Empower your professional journey. 
  * Mentoring Programs: Propel your development with guidance. 
  * Friendly Supportive Team: Join a culture that thrives on collaboration. 
  * Exposure to Iconic Projects: Immerse yourself in impactful work. 
  * Employee Social Club: Connect and celebrate with peers. 

** About You and The Role **

** To be successful in this role, you will have the following skills: **

  * Australian-recognised degree in Engineering or relevant trade background. 
  * Hold national and/or regional registrations and qualifications. (CPEng, NER, RPEQ or QBCC Designers License). 
  * Excellent problem-solving skills. 
  * Excellent communication, written and people skills. 
  * Australian citizen (preferred) or permanent resident. 
  * Thorough understanding and application of the regulations, Australian standards, and the National Construction Code. 
  * Understanding of Engineering modelling software (including CAD/REVIT). 
  * Diverse experience in a range of project types. 
  * Demonstrated capability in independently managing your disciplines elements on projects. 
  * Demonstrated capability in independently being able to manage a project throughout the design life cycle right the way through construction to practical completion. 
  * A commitment to accuracy, high standards of written and verbal communication, punctuality, organisation, presentation and to ongoing development and improvement in these areas with a view to your refinement of a well-rounded base of consulting skills and technical knowledge. 

** The key responsibilities will include: **

  * Utilising your demonstrated organisational capability and engaging approach to delivering projects. 
  * Training and supervision of graduate engineers assisting with projects under your direction. 
  * Applying technical excellence in Electrical Services design. 
  * Conduct Quality Assurance (QA) review on Electrical deliverables in alignment with Lucid’s QA policy. 
  * Provide certification of design through Form 15 signoff. 
  * Client/contractor interface. 
  * Preparation of fee proposals and project bids. 
  * Managing a team, working with other engineers in a design team, taking and proving direction from and as a project team leader and providing guidance for junior engineers. 
  * Attendance at site inspections and project meetings, and preparation/review of reports and minutes. 
  * Attendance at industry events as a Lucid representative. 

** About Us: **

Lucid is one of Australia's fastest-growing national engineering and advisory
practices with over 300 staff across offices in Melbourne, Adelaide, Alice
Springs, Canberra, Darwin, Brisbane, Perth, and Sydney. As a professional
services organisation, we understand that our people are our greatest asset.
We invest in our people by providing various opportunities for growth and
development and value the importance of celebrating success. We pride
ourselves on our reputation, work culture, strong business ethos, and diverse
project portfolio. Our vision is to become Australia’s most forward-thinking,
agile, and influential engineers and asset advisors. Our team is dedicated to
offering exceptional customer care and high-quality service.

** Ready to help us create a Better World? **

Lucid is committed to creating a Better World. As a team member, you'll be
central to helping with our sustainability goals, Reconciliation Action Plan,
and providing an inclusive working environment. Our senior members are also
involved in an internal mentoring program to help foster growth across all
roles.

We embrace diversity and encourage applications from individuals of all
backgrounds.

